00:33:13.280 --> 00:33:14.610
PROFESSOR: I guess I could.

00:33:14.610 --> 00:33:17.341
I have an easier
way of doing things.

00:33:17.341 --> 00:33:17.840
OK.

00:33:17.840 --> 00:33:20.540
So the easier way that
I have on doing things

00:33:20.540 --> 00:33:23.860
is we have emphasized
that in thermodynamics, we

00:33:23.860 --> 00:33:26.570
can look at different
perspectives.

00:33:26.570 --> 00:33:30.780
Problem with this
perspective of the canonical

00:33:30.780 --> 00:33:34.880
is that I know that I will
encounter this singularity.

00:33:34.880 --> 00:33:35.540
I know that.

00:33:35.540 --> 00:33:38.450
There's phase diagrams
like this exist.

00:33:38.450 --> 00:33:43.070
Whereas if I use this
prescription I have one.

00:33:43.070 --> 00:33:45.370
So what's the difference
is this prescription

00:33:45.370 --> 00:33:49.240
is better mind in terms of
pressure and temperature.

00:33:49.240 --> 00:33:52.500
So what I want to
do is to replace

00:33:52.500 --> 00:33:55.380
the canonical
perspective with what

00:33:55.380 --> 00:34:00.080
I will call the isobaric-- it's
the Gibbs canonical ensemble.

00:34:00.080 --> 00:34:04.220
In this context it's
called isobaric ensemble

00:34:04.220 --> 00:34:08.469
where rather than describing
things at fixed volume,

00:34:08.469 --> 00:34:11.560
I describe things
at fixed pressure.

00:34:11.560 --> 00:34:14.010
So I tell you what
pressure, temperature,

00:34:14.010 --> 00:34:16.710
and the number of
particles are and then

00:34:16.710 --> 00:34:21.440
I calculate the corresponding
Gibbs partition function.

00:34:25.030 --> 00:34:27.449
Why does that help?

00:34:27.449 --> 00:34:30.690
Why that helps is because of
what you see on the left side

00:34:30.690 --> 00:34:33.900
diagram is if I
wanted to maintain

00:34:33.900 --> 00:34:36.120
this system at the
fixed pressure rather

00:34:36.120 --> 00:34:38.810
than a fixed volume,
I would replace

00:34:38.810 --> 00:34:42.900
one of the walls of this
container with a piston

00:34:42.900 --> 00:34:45.520
and then I would apply a
particular value of pressure.

00:34:48.060 --> 00:34:50.620
Then you can see that a
situation such as this

00:34:50.620 --> 00:34:53.179
does not occur.

00:34:53.179 --> 00:34:58.300
The piston will move
so that ultimately I

00:34:58.300 --> 00:35:00.650
have a uniform density.

00:35:00.650 --> 00:35:05.820
If I'm choosing my
pressure to be up here,

00:35:05.820 --> 00:35:07.100
then it would be all liquid.

00:35:07.100 --> 00:35:10.700
If I choose my pressure to be
down here, it will be all gas.

00:35:10.700 --> 00:35:13.220
So I have this piston on top.

00:35:13.220 --> 00:35:16.250
It does not tolerate
coexistence.

00:35:16.250 --> 00:35:19.260
It will either keep
everybody in the gas phase

00:35:19.260 --> 00:35:21.590
