01:02:42.160 --> 01:02:50.430
It is minus k V T divided by
V minus b squared plus 2 a

01:02:50.430 --> 01:02:54.920
over V cubed so I
took one derivative.

01:02:54.920 --> 01:02:58.510
And the second derivative
is now constrained also,

01:02:58.510 --> 01:03:03.090
so that's going to
give me plus 2 k T V

01:03:03.090 --> 01:03:10.130
minus b cubed minus
6 a V to the fourth.

01:03:10.130 --> 01:03:12.040
OK?

01:03:12.040 --> 01:03:17.580
Now if I'm at a critical
point-- so I put c over here,

01:03:17.580 --> 01:03:22.950
this will be 0, and
this will also be 0.

01:03:25.860 --> 01:03:29.010
So the conditions for
the critical point

01:03:29.010 --> 01:03:39.350
are that first of all k B Tc
divided by Vc minus b cubed

01:03:39.350 --> 01:03:44.300
should be 2 a over
Vc cubed and 2

01:03:44.300 --> 01:03:51.680
k B Tc Vc minus b to the
fourth power should be 6 a

01:03:51.680 --> 01:03:55.958
divided by Vc to
the fourth power.

01:03:55.958 --> 01:03:58.940
Hmm?

01:03:58.940 --> 01:04:05.460
So this is two equations for two
