01:04:05.460 --> 01:04:08.990
We can actually reduce
it to one variable

01:04:08.990 --> 01:04:12.580
by dividing these two
equations with each other.

01:04:12.580 --> 01:04:14.520
The division of
the left-hand sides

01:04:14.520 --> 01:04:20.580
will give me Vc minus b
in the numerator divided

01:04:20.580 --> 01:04:24.370
by 2 in the denominator.

01:04:24.370 --> 01:04:31.850
The ratio of these two
is simply Vc over 3.

01:04:31.850 --> 01:04:34.610
That's a one variable equation.

01:04:34.610 --> 01:04:35.575
Yes?

